{{Infobox football biography | name= Al Greene | image = | fullname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1978|5|5|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Gibraltar]] | height = | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]], [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | currentclub = [[St Joseph's F.C.|St Joseph's]] | clubnumber = 21 | years1 = 1995–1997 | caps1 = | goals1 = | clubs1 = [[St Theresa's F.C.|St Theresa's]] | years2 = 1997–1998 | caps2 = | goals2 = | clubs2 = [[Glacis United F.C.|Glacis United]] | years3 = 1998–2000 | caps3 = | goals3 = | clubs3 = [[Real Balompédica Linense|Linense]] | years4 = 2000–2001 | caps4 = | goals4 = | clubs4 = [[Glacis United F.C.|Glacis United]] | years5 = 2001–2004 | caps5 = | goals5 = | clubs5 = [[Real Balompédica Linense|Linense]] | years6 = 2004–2005 | caps6 = | goals6 = | clubs6 = [[Juventud Palmones F.C.|Palmones]] | years7 = 2005–2016 | caps7 = | goals7 = | clubs7 = [[Glacis United F.C.|Glacis United]] | years8 = 2016–2018 | caps8 = 38 | goals8 = 0 | clubs8 = [[Lions Gibraltar F.C.|Lions Gibraltar]] | years9 = 2018– | caps9 = 1 | goals9 = 0 | clubs9 = [[St Joseph's F.C.|St Joseph's]] <!--all match stats are taken from the GFA website's fixtures/results page. There is no single appearances page, so refer to each individual match page--> | nationalyears1 = 2013 | nationalteam1 = [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = 13 August 2018 | ntupdate = 21 November 2016 }} '''Al Greene''' (born 5 May 1978)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/8718/Al_Greene.html | title=Al Greene | publisher=National-football-teams | accessdate=20 November 2013}}</ref> is a Gibraltarian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://nonfifafootball.blogspot.co.nz/2013/11/gibraltar-produced-memorable.html | title=Historic draw for Gibraltar in first UEFA game | publisher=Nonfifafootball.blogspot.co.nz | accessdate=20 November 2013}}</ref> for [[St Joseph's F.C.|St Joseph's]] and [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]].
==Club career== Starting his career in Gibraltar with St Theresa's FC, Greene had two spells at Spanish club [[Real Balompédica Linense|Linense]], as well as three spells at [[Glacis United F.C.|Glacis United]] during his career. In 2016 he joined [[Lions Gibraltar F.C.|Lions Gibraltar]]. Although he was used primarily as a defender, he became a regular feature in the side. He left the club aged 40 in July 2018, but announced his intention to keep playing.<ref>[http://footballgibraltar.com/2018/07/greene-i-would-give-anything-to-be-20-years-younger-and-have-the-same-opportunities/ GREENE: "I WOULD GIVE ANYTHING TO BE 20 YEARS YOUNGER AND HAVE THE SAME OPPORTUNITIES"] Football Gibraltar. 17 July 2018. Retrieved 17 July 2018.</ref> On 6 August 2018, he joined [[St Joseph's F.C.|St Joseph's]].<ref>[https://twitter.com/StJosephsFCGib/status/1026488721712013312 Al Greene joins St Joseph's] St Joseph's FC on Twitter. 6 August 2018. Retrieved 6 August 2018.</ref>
==International career== Greene made his international debut with Gibraltar, at the age of 35, on 19 November 2013 in a [[2013 Gibraltar v Slovakia football match|0–0 home draw]] with [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://sports.yahoo.com/news/rock-solid-gibraltar-hold-slovakia-memorable-draw-debut-210329099--sow.html | title=Rock-solid Gibraltar hold Slovakia to memorable draw on debut | publisher=Sports Yahoo | accessdate=21 November 2013}}</ref> This was Gibraltar's first game since being admitted to [[UEFA]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/qualifiers/news/newsid=2024868.html | title=Gibraltar hold Slovakia in maiden international | publisher=www.uefa.com | accessdate=20 November 2013}}</ref> This would prove to be his only cap for Gibraltar as a UEFA association. {{External media|image1 = [http://www.smh.com.au/photogallery/sport/soccer/shock-of-gibraltar-20131120-2xusj.html?selectedImage=3 Greene celebrates with supporters after international debut]|align = right|topic=International debut}}
