The '''Manitoba Sports [[Hall of Fame]] and Museum''' is a museum in [[Winnipeg]], [[Manitoba]], Canada, dedicated to the history of sport in Manitoba and honouring the best in sport. The organization began in 1980 and in 1993, a museum was opened in [[The Forks, Winnipeg|The Forks]]. After five years, the museum moved to [[Hudson's Bay (retailer)|The Bay]] store on Portage Avenue.

However, the museum has moved to the Sport Manitoba building, and had a grand opening on October 27, 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.halloffame.mb.ca/news_view.php?id=528 |title=Manitoba Sports Hall of Fame Grand Opening |author= |date= |work= |publisher= |accessdate=8 May 2013}}</ref>

Exhibits of Manitoba's sports teams and honoured athletes are displayed in the museum.

