{{Infobox rugby team | teamname = Tucumán Lawn Tennis | image = Tuc lawntenis logo.svg | imagesize = 120px | location = [[San Miguel de Tucumán]], [[Argentina]] | countryflag = Argentina | fullname = Tucumán Lawn Tennis Club | union = [[Unión de Rugby de Tucumán]] | shortname = Tennis Tucumán | founded = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|1915|5|20}} | ground = El Salvador | url = http://www.tucumanlawntennis.org.ar/ | president = Rafael Tissera | coach = | league = [[Torneo del Noroeste]] | season = 2014 | position = 1st |pattern_la1=_navyyellowhoops|pattern_b1=_navyyellowhoops|pattern_ra1=_navyyellowhoops|leftarm1=|body1=|rightarm1=|shorts1=ffffff| pattern_so1=|socks1=000066 |pattern_la2= |pattern_b2=|pattern_ra2= |leftarm2= |body2= |rightarm2= |shorts2=|pattern_so2=|socks2= }}
'''Tucumán Lawn Tennis Club''', or simply '''Tennis Tucumán''', is a [[sports club]] from [[San Miguel de Tucumán]], [[Argentina]]. Founded in 1915 as a [[tennis]] club, Tucumán LT is now mostly known for its [[rugby union]] team, registered with the [[Unión de Rugby de Tucumán]]<ref name="Club History">{{cite news|url=http://www.urtuc.com.ar/tennis.html |title=Club History | language=Spanish |date=21 May 2010 |accessdate=22 May 2010}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> and currently playing in the [[Torneo del Noroeste]] tournament.
Apart from tennis and rugby, the hosts other activities such as [[athletics (sport)|athletics]], [[field hockey]], [[association football|football]], [[gymnastics]], [[golf]], [[paddle tennis]], [[squash (sport)|squash]] and [[swimming (sport)|swimming]].
==History== Tucumán Lawn Tennis Club was founded in San Miguel de Tucumán on 20 May 1915, as a multi-sports club, by English expatriates and young locals. The first sports played at the club were [[lawn tennis]] and [[cricket]].
Originally located near Tucumán's Savoy Hotel, the club moved to the Parque 9 de Julio, in 1930. In 1987, 10 more hectares were purchased nearby and most installations, except for the clubhouse, were moved there.
Rugby first appeared at the club in 1961 and is now the sport for which the club is mostly known. in 1973 the club would go on to win its first provincial title.
==Titles== *'''[[Torneo del Noroeste]] (11)''': 1973, 1977, 1979, 1980, 1981, 1982, 2008, 2009, 2011 , 2012, 2014.
