{{orphan|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Wanzhou Sports Center | native_name = 万州体育中心 | image = | pushpin_map = China Chongqing#China | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Chongqing | pushpin_label_position = | address = | location = [[Wanzhou District]], [[Chongqing]], China | coordinates = {{Coord|30.7876|108.3952|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = March 2010 | opened = October 2012 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | tenants = | seating_capacity = 26,000 | website = }} The '''Wanzhou Sports Center''' ({{zh|s=万州体育中心}}) is a sports venue in [[Wanzhou District]], [[Chongqing]], China, on the bank of the [[Yangtze]] River. It has a [[multi-purpose stadium]] with a seating capacity of 26,000, and a [[natatorium]] with 1,650 seats. Construction began in March 2010, and the center was opened in October 2012.<ref name=cnki>{{cite journal |url=http://www.cnki.com.cn/Article/CJFDTotal-JZCS201317012.htm |title=重庆万州体育中心 |journal=城市建筑 (Urbanism and Architecture) |issue=17 |year=2013 |author1=Li Yanyun |author2=Luo Yang |author3=Zhao Ziteng |issn=1673-0232}}</ref>
